James de Villiers, News24 A security guard stands near one of the hijacked trucks. (Photo supplied) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg &ndash; Gauteng police are following several leads in their bid to arrest more suspects involved in a truck hijacking on the N1 in Johannesburg on Thursday. Two people, aged 35 and 42, were arrested earlier, Gauteng police said in a statement.&nbsp;Two trucks loaded with cellphones were hijacked on the N1 next to the Buccleuch interchange on Thursday morning.Officers followed a tracking signal to a cemetery at the Marlboro off-ramp in Alexandra, where a shootout occurred, the Johannesburg Metro Police Department (JMPD) said.A 28-year-old JMPD officer was shot in the upper body and taken to Milpark Hospital. He was wearing a bulletproof vest.&nbsp;Emer-G-Med spokesperson Max Cohen said the driver of one of the trucks and a security guard escorting the trucks were shot. Both were in a critical condition.Police asked for anyone with information about the crime to contact Crime Stop on 08600-10111 or by sending an SMS to Crime Line at 32211.&nbsp;24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.